en:
The federal government's answer to a minor inquiry on assaults on asylum seekers reveals that the responsible police department is investigating charges of anti-constitutional denigration of constitutional organs without any local connection to an asylum shelter. The incident is initially classified as "politically motivated crime - right-wing" in the federal government's response to a minor inquiry. In a later answer of the federal government, the incident is completely missing. When asked by the Amadeu Antonio Foundation, the responsible press office of the Dresden police says: "Why the case is missing from the federal government's answer in the 3rd quarter, we can unfortunately not clarify."
