The Federal Government's answer to a small inquiry about attacks on asylum seekers and their accommodation shows that the responsible police department is investigating property damage and classifies this incident as "politically motivated crime - right-wing". The answer does not contain any further details about the course of events. Due to the large number of incidents, it is not possible for us to find out more details in every case by asking the responsible investigating authorities (or the responsible public prosecutor's office). As a rule, we therefore limit our investigations to particularly serious incidents, such as bodily harm or arson attacks.
